casebody.data:
John H. Johnson, plaintiff, vs. Patrick Casey, defendant.

(Before Monell, J. at special term,

An injunction dissolved on the grounds: 1. That the affidavit and papers on which it was granted were illegible. 2. That the injunction had not been served on the defendant personally. 3. That the papers had not been filed, as required by the rules of the court.

March —, 1865.)
